Main problem was that the Bureau of Meteorology could not forecast exactly where the storm would form . 
 Storm was forecast to gather between Port Macquarie and Newcastle, but it formed just north of Newcastle . 
 It then covered 150km south from Newcastle to Wollongong where a third of Australia’s population live . 
 When the storm hit it caused the maximum amount of destruction because of it being a huge suburban area . 
 Budget cuts also meant the Bureau of Meteorology did not have as many resources at its disposal . 
